



Philadelphia, 19 July 1775



Introduces the bearers, Mr Ogden & Mr Burr of the Jerseys, who Visit the Camp not as Spectators, but with a View of Joining the Army & being Active during the Campaign.1 . . . Your Dispatches Reachd me last Eveng. I shall forward
[133]
you the Papers immediately. The Results of Congress you shall know as early as possible.2
